Results.ReviewText:
Lifted lid reveals large granule promises : deep colour and intense Robusta+Arabica strength and aroma.



Pouring on hot milk, or water, delivers on those promises


Rich dark colour, roasty aroma, and classic coffee taste; small, black and strong, or frothy latte - a coffee for all tastes and ocassions.


Closing jar ensures protected freshness, colour, and, aroma : cup after cup - time after time.
Results.Title: THE Gold Standard with instant coffee

Results.ReviewText: We usually buy different coffees depending on the offer that is on. This particular coffee was on offer at our local supermarket to decided to give it a go. We are so pleased that we did!  The taste and quality of the product was well worth what we paid and even when the offer was finished we continued to purchase this Gold Blend. It deserves the title of `Gold` as it comes first place in our choice of coffee.
Results.Title: Tastes Just Like Freshly Ground

Results.ReviewText:
I always buy Nescafe Gold Blend on every shopping trip, the new blend is as good, if not better than the old recipe.
Nescafe still has the best tasting coffees of all the other coffee producers and is still very competitive priced.
I like my coffee quite strong so I add 1+1/2 teaspoons of coffee and 1 spoon of sugar with a small amount of milk for a beautiful smooth taste. Try it I think you might like it.
Results.Title: Golden coffee taste

Results.ReviewText: I buy this regularly as my husband takes coffee to work as well as both of us drinking it at home. Lovely smooth taste, hubby won't have any other!  One gripe is the price now, the flavour has improved slightly; not that it really needed improving, but I really don't think the price increase is warranted. Value for money is not good as there are several good coffees on the market now at a much better price.
Results.Title: smooth taste

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks very much for letting us know your thoughts on the new recipe Bernie. We really appreciate your feedback! The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: The only coffee I have loved for more years than I can remember is Gold Blend. Now it has changed. It is bitter, sludgy and has lost the beautiful aroma and taste. I saw the new style labels and bought two jars. What a disappointment. It is awful. I cannot drink it so have wasted my money. Unless it goes back to the original I will not buy Nescafé again. I’ve rated it 1 star as the ratings won’t allow zero.
Results.Title: If it’s not broken don’t mend it.

Results.ReviewText: Unless I hear that the recipe has reverted to the nice one without grouts, I won’t buy again
Results.Title: Bad change

Results.ReviewText: I’ve been buying this blend of coffee for as long as I can remember and I just love the taste and texture at any point in the day. Breakfast, mid morning, lunch afternoon or after dinner. It’s smooth and rich without being overpowering. And it remains consistently great when so many other coffees changed .... and not for the better. Whilst all Nescafé coffees are great this one firmly remains my favourite.
Results.Title: Reliably good

Results.ReviewText: I can't remember when I first drank a cup of Nescafe, but I have been a faithful fan of Regular Nescafe for years.  Recently, at a friend's house, I tried Nescafe Gold Blend.  WOW! Old friends are good, but new ones are better! Why haven't I tried Nescafe Gold Blend before? It's certainly worth that tiny bit of extra cost for that fantabulous extra flavour!  I'm sticking with the Gold Standard from now on!
Results.Title: Why haven't I tried this before?

Results.ReviewText: I had foresaken my usual Nescafé Gold Blend, being tempted by other brands on offer, as you do.  But last week, there was my old friend, competitively priced, so I came home with my purchase.  At our mid-morning coffee break, my husband who generally wouldn't notice what coffee I gave him, commented on the lovely rich aroma and delicious taste.  So I promise I won't ever stray away from Gold Blend again.
Results.Title: An old friend

Results.ReviewText: Without a doubt the best coffee on the market, we have tried others when on offers or if, God forbid the shop has run out of Gold Blend!, but it's just not right!  I don't drink as much of it as my husband does, it is his favorite drink of choice due to it's smooth rich flavour, with a touch of creamy sweetness and also with a dash of -is it filtered  coffee hmm on the side, which I totally agree with.
Results.Title: Smooth  and Tasty

Results.ReviewText: We’ve been Gold Blend coffee drinkers for many years. We have tried other brands but have always returned to this coffee for the great taste. However we’ve have noticed, since the rebranding, that there has been a residue at the bottom of the cup. As well as being unpleasant this suggests that the coffee is not the same as previously. Is this residue an insoluble additive to the manufacturing process?
Results.Title: Re branding

Results.ReviewText: I am a huge fan if gold blend and I cannot function until I have had at least 2 cups in the morning. One in peace before I get my children up and dressed and then one before we leave for work and school, sometimes taking one in a thermal cup with me. I thought I had bought two 'fake' jars of coffee but after seeing a couple of other reviews on here I know I am not alone. Please bring back the old one!
Results.Title: I miss my old Gold blend!!

ClientResponses.Response: Thanks for taking the time & leaving your thoughts on the new recipe. We really value all feedback we're getting on the changes we've made.

Results.ReviewText: Have used Gold Blend for as long as you have been making it but like other customers will now be trying others.Why alter a succesful blend still trading it as the same coffee. As far as many of us are concerned this has only been done for cost savings , if we wished to change our regular coffee we could quite easily have tried one of your other coffees  we do not want you to make the decision for us!
Results.Title: Recipe Change

Results.ReviewText: It's just really simple. I get up early. Even if it's dark, I go into the kitchen, boil a kettle, spoon my Nescafe Gold into my favourite mug, and go to do some work before I leave for more work! That mug of coffee, with its gorgeous aroma, perfect coffee taste and warm bounce of stimulation, is the best companion you can have at a time like that – and it always means it's going to be a great day
Results.Title: Happiness in a mug

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, it's disappointing for us to hear this but thank you very much for leaving your comments & letting us know!

Results.ReviewText: Gold Blend has been my only choice for so many years. However this week have opened the new shaped jar, (more difficult to open) and the coffee is awful. I drink my coffee hot and quickly and still there is a horrible sludge towards the bottom of the cup. Nescafe seem to compare this new coffee to barista style coffee. If I wanted such coffee I would buy it. Definitely looking for another brand.
Results.Title: Please bring back original Gold Blend

Results.ReviewText: This is my favourite coffee. I especially love the cup I have first thing in the morning.No sugar just cold milk. I always feel I am drinking a quality coffee. In the days when my children were small getting a hot cup of coffee was always difficult, so I really appreciate a hot cup of Nescafe Gold now.Even the jar feels nice to handle, and is nice to use to store other foods in once it is empty.
Results.Title: My favourite coffee bar none

Results.ReviewText: Once I found Gold Blend 37 with the Green Label years ago I knew my search for the perfect coffee was over - there have been numerous iterations of flavours and styles over the years and whilst some of them are quite good such as Nescafe Azera and Millicano the original Gold Blend instant is still the best coffee you can get in granule form and especially at the very reasonable price it is too.
Results.Title: Simply The Best

Results.ReviewText: Have  been  using  Nescafe  Gold  Blend  for  years,  any  have  never found another  instant  coffee  that  compares.  The  taste  is far  superior  to  other  brands,  and  we  have  already  stocked  up  with  the  new  promotions.  Small  tip, if  you  drink  Gold  Blend  black,  pour a  drop  of  cold  water over  the  granules  before  the  hot,  it  ensures you  get  the  full  flavour.
Results.Title: Smart  New  Jar

Results.ReviewText: We have drunk Nescafé Gold Blend and Nescafé Gold Blend Decaf for many years and would not use anything else till now. The new Nescafé Gold Blend and Nescafé Gold Blend Decaf seem to have sludge at the bottom of the cup, and we don’t like it. The flavour is exceptional as it always has been but we pray they decide to go back to the way it used to be without the sludge in the bottom of the cup.
Results.Title: Disappointed

Results.ReviewText:
Feeling a bit under the weather, I was making a pork pie. I needed Gelatine so visited local Tesco. 
Next door was having their drive tarmac'd. There were lorries everywhere. I succeeded in reversing into one of the lorries. There was broken plastic everywhere.
At Tesco, two young ladies on a Nescafe promotion stand offered me chance to win a prize.
I purchased a jar of my usual Nescafe and returned to claim my prize.
My first take on returning home was to make myself a nice hot cup of Nescafe. Always deliciously comforting, the aroma filled the kitchen with a sense of peace and well being as, with eyes closed and thinking of my holiday in couple of weeks, I relaxed into peaceful oblivion.
The Prize? Oh I won a £100. This will pay for the broken light cluster on my car.
So Gold Blend is not only the best coffee on the market, but it is also a Fairy Godmother! 
PURE GOLD from a GOLD JAR
Results.Title: BE LUCKY......... BUY NESCAFE

Results.ReviewText: After reading some of the reviews i wonder if i am drinking the same beverage , this coffee as a very mild taste compared with some coffees that are bitter , i have tried different brands of coffee , but i always come back to my nescafe  , it makes you feel special when drinking it , my friends drink specialised coffees , but they too like the taste of Gold blend , its in a class of its own .
Results.Title: Very enjoyable cup of coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you for taking the time & letting us know your thoughts on the changes we've made. All your comments have been noted & will be passed to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: This is the first time that I have felt compelled to write a review.  I have been a loyal customer of Gold Blend for over 40 years but now I will have to look for a new brand.  The changed recipe tastes cheap, thin and bitter, and the addition of insoluble dregs to the coffee completes the deal breaker.  I will not be buying new Gold Blend again unless you reinstate the previous formulation?
Results.Title: Really Disappointed with the New Recipe

Results.ReviewText: I saw the coffee to taste on entering Tesco, had one sip and instantly loved the flavour, it was refreshing and smooth. I purchased Gold Blend and dont think it will be long before I have to go back to buy another as this wont last long! Good value for money too compared to other brands. Even my wife who doesnt really like coffee had some and loved it - so I'll probably have to share it now!
Results.Title: Fantastic taste

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks very much for getting in touch & leaving your thoughts on the new recipe! It saddens us to hear you're not a fan of the changes we've made but we appreciate your feedback. The residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee!

Results.ReviewText: Oh Nescafe what have you done to Gold Blend ? Used to love the deep rich taste of this coffee and now it is bitter and leaves a horrible residue in my cup. Looking at the review on here most people seem to agree your new blend is awful. Please, please revert back to your original recipe - until then I will have to find a suitable replacement as I can no longer drink this pseudo coffee.......
Results.Title: Horrible taste pithy residue

Results.ReviewText: I tried this coffee after using another well known brand for quite awhile. From the first mouthful to the end of my 3rd delicious cup of coffee that morning, it perked me up no end. The other coffee that I was so used to seemed boring and even the thought of it while I was drinking Nescafé gold had me thinking 'why didn't I not try Nescafé sooner '!! It's Nescafé gold for me all the way now.
Results.Title: "It's a real perk me up start to the day"

Results.ReviewText: I have recently returned to buying Nescafe Gold Blend after trying other brands,  but none of them compare to the smooth taste of Nescafe Gold Blend.  This coffee does not have the bitter after taste of other coffees and recently it seems to have improved and tastes even better. I like nothing better after a long day to relax and enjoy a lovely mug  of the best instant coffee on the market.
Results.Title: Nescafe Gold just gets better.

Results.ReviewText: I've never really tried other blends of Nescafe having been a fan of their instant normal blends most of my life, but decided to try 'Gold Blend' and was amazed at the full body richness of it and the enhanced taste over the one I was used to. Whilst a little more, I think the added smoothness and more intense flavour was worth it and I may now switch to only 'Gold', I think I deserve it...
Results.Title: Pleasantly surprised at the rich taste...

ClientResponses.Response: Thank you very much for getting in touch with us & letting us know what you think of the new recipe.

Results.ReviewText: If I wanted a 'barista style expresso experience' I'd buy a barista coffee. I have drunk Gold Blend for perhaps the past 25 years but this new blend gives me headaches and I don't like the sludge at the bottom. Please can you give this new blend an alternative name and also continue to provide the old-style blend that was just fine. In the meantime I'm afraid I need to find an alternative.
Results.Title: Leave well alone!

Results.ReviewText: We have tried 3 jars now, for a fair comparison and I'm afraid we don't like it as much as the older version. The new version leaves a scummy film in the cup, it also leaves a gritty dust in the bottom. It also doesn't taste good, it has a rougher taste to it, not as smooth as it used to be. If there was a choice of old and new on the shelf I would pick the old one over this every time.
Results.Title: Dusty and gritty

Results.ReviewText:
As a regular user of Nescafe i thought i would buy and try this one for a change. 
I found it great value for money per serving, Also found it had great body and smooth taste.  A tip i use is to put a level tea spoon of coffee in first then add the water which has cooled, then add milk as required while stirring, this means you can have as strong or weak coffee as your taste buds wish
Results.Title: Fantastic taste
